{{Cite sources|date=2019th year 10月7日 (月) 03:20 (UTC)}} {{Infobox noble | name = Tsuchimikado Arinaga | image = | caption = | period = {{ill|Sengoku period (Japan)|ja|戦国時代}} - {{ill|Azuchi-Momoyama period|ja|安土桃山時代}} | birth_date = {{ill|Daiei|ja|大永}} 7 ({{ill|1527|ja|1527th year }}) | death_date = {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正}} 5, {{ill|January 2 (Lunisolar)|ja|1月2日}} ({{ill|1577|ja|1577th year }} {{ill|January 20|ja|1月20日}}) | rank = {{ill|Shōsanmi|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank}}, {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議}}, {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽頭}}, {{ill|Gyōbukyō|ja|刑部卿}} | lord = {{ill|Emperor Go-Nara|ja|後奈良天皇}} | family = {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏}}, {{ill|Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家 (安倍氏)}} | parents = Father: {{ill|Tsuchimikado Ariharu|ja|土御門有春}} | siblings = {{ill|Kadenokōji Akitaka|ja|勘解由小路在高}} | spouse = Seishunin | children = {{ill|Tsuchimikado Hisanaga|ja|土御門久脩}}, Daughter (married to {{ill|Kanjūji Harutoyo|ja|勧修寺晴豊}}) }}
'''Tsuchimikado Arinaga''' (土御門 有脩) was a noble and {{ill|Onmyōji|ja|陰陽師}} active during the {{ill|Sengoku period (Japan)|ja|戦国時代}} and the {{ill|Azuchi-Momoyama period|ja|安土桃山時代}}. He was the head of the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮}} and the 30th head of the {{ill|Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家 (安倍氏)}}, which descended from the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏}}.
== Biography == Tsuchimikado Arinaga held the ranks of {{ill|Shōsanmi|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank}}, {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議}}, and {{ill|Gyōbukyō|ja|刑部卿}}. He was the head of a {{ill|dōjō family|ja|堂上家}} of the {{ill|han-ke|ja|半家}} rank, belonging to the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏}} lineage.
In {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天文}} 11 ({{ill|1542|ja|1542nd year }}), during a period of war and instability, Arinaga left Kyoto and withdrew to his estate in {{ill|Nata-shō|ja|名田庄村}}, {{ill|Wakasa Province|ja|若狭国}}. This led to his abandonment of duties as {{ill|Onmyō no kami|ja|陰陽頭}}. Consequently, {{ill|Kadenokōji Akitomi|ja|勘解由小路在富}}, a noble of the {{ill|Kamo clan|ja|賀茂朝臣氏}} lineage residing in {{ill|Sagami Province|ja|相模国}}, was summoned to Kyoto to take over the Onmyōryō's responsibilities.
== Lineage == === Family=== * Father: {{ill|Tsuchimikado Ariharu|ja|土御門有春}} * Mother: Unknown * Wife: Seishunin * Children: ''' {{ill|Tsuchimikado Hisanaga|ja|土御門久脩}} ''' Daughter: Married to {{ill|Kanjūji Harutoyo|ja|勧修寺晴豊}}
=== Descendants=== The male-line descendants of {{ill|Abe no Seimei|ja|安倍晴明}} through Tsuchimikado Arinaga have largely been lost. Notably, the {{ill|Kurahashi family|ja|倉橋家}} (a cadet branch of the Abe clan) and the {{ill|Kanjūji family|ja|勧修寺家}} trace their lineage through Arinaga's children and subsequent marriages. The family line continued through daughter’s descendants and their connections to prominent aristocratic families, including the {{ill|Imperial House of Japan|ja|皇室}} from {{ill|Emperor Ninkō|ja|仁孝天皇}} onwards.
