'''Tsuchimikado Arinaga''' (土御門 有脩) was a noble and {{ill|Onmyōji|ja|陰陽師|12=draft}} active during the {{ill|Sengoku period (Japan)|ja|戦国時代|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Azuchi-Momoyama period|ja|安土桃山時代|12=draft}}. He was the head of the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|12=draft}} and the 30th head of the {{ill|Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家 (安倍氏)|12=draft}}, which descended from the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏|12=draft}}.

== Biography ==
Tsuchimikado Arinaga held the ranks of {{ill|Shōsanmi|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Gyōbukyō|ja|刑部卿|12=draft}}. He was the head of a {{ill|dōjō family|ja|堂上家|12=draft}} of the {{ill|han-ke|ja|半家|12=draft}} rank, belonging to the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏|12=draft}} lineage.

In {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天文|12=draft}} 11 ({{ill|1542|ja|1542nd year|12=draft}}), during a period of war and instability, Arinaga left Kyoto and withdrew to his estate in {{ill|Nata-shō|ja|名田庄村|12=draft}}, {{ill|Wakasa Province|ja|若狭国|12=draft}}. This led to his abandonment of duties as {{ill|Onmyō no kami|ja|陰陽頭|12=draft}}. Consequently, {{ill|Kadenokōji Akitomi|ja|勘解由小路在富|12=draft}}, a noble of the {{ill|Kamo clan|ja|賀茂朝臣氏|12=draft}} lineage residing in {{ill|Sagami Province|ja|相模国|12=draft}}, was summoned to Kyoto to take over the Onmyōryō's responsibilities.

== Lineage ==
=== Family===
* Father: {{ill|Tsuchimikado Ariharu|ja|土御門有春|12=draft}}
* Mother: Unknown
* Wife: Seishunin
* Children:
''' {{ill|Tsuchimikado Hisanaga|ja|土御門久脩|12=draft}}
''' Daughter: Married to {{ill|Kanjūji Harutoyo|ja|勧修寺晴豊|12=draft}}

=== Descendants===
The male-line descendants of {{ill|Abe no Seimei|ja|安倍晴明|12=draft}} through Tsuchimikado Arinaga have largely been lost. Notably, the {{ill|Kurahashi family|ja|倉橋家|12=draft}} (a cadet branch of the Abe clan) and the {{ill|Kanjūji family|ja|勧修寺家|12=draft}} trace their lineage through Arinaga's children and subsequent marriages. The family line continued through daughter’s descendants and their connections to prominent aristocratic families, including the {{ill|Imperial House of Japan|ja|皇室|12=draft}} from {{ill|Emperor Ninkō|ja|仁孝天皇|12=draft}} onwards.

