Tsuchimikado Arinaga held the ranks of {{ill|Shōsanmi|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Gyōbukyō|ja|刑部卿|12=draft|12=draft}}. He was the head of a {{ill|dōjō family|ja|堂上家|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|han-ke|ja|半家|12=draft|12=draft}} rank, belonging to the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏|12=draft|12=draft}} lineage.

In {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天文|12=draft|12=draft}} 11 ({{ill|1542|ja|1542nd year|12=draft|12=draft}}), during a period of war and instability, Arinaga left Kyoto and withdrew to his estate in {{ill|Nata-shō|ja|名田庄村|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Wakasa Province|ja|若狭国|12=draft|12=draft}}. This led to his abandonment of duties as {{ill|Onmyō no kami|ja|陰陽頭|12=draft|12=draft}}. Consequently, {{ill|Kadenokōji Akitomi|ja|勘解由小路在富|12=draft|12=draft}}, a noble of the {{ill|Kamo clan|ja|賀茂朝臣氏|12=draft|12=draft}} lineage residing in {{ill|Sagami Province|ja|相模国|12=draft|12=draft}}, was summoned to Kyoto to take over the Onmyōryō's responsibilities.

== Lineage ==
