In {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天文|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun|qq=}} 11 ([[:en:1542|1542]]), during a period of war and instability, Arinaga left Kyoto and withdrew to his estate in [[:en:Natashō, Fukui|Nata-shō]], [[:en:Wakasa Province|Wakasa Province]]. This led to his abandonment of duties as {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Onmyō no kami|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō no kami|qq=}}. Consequently, {{ill|Kadenokōji Akitomi|ja|勘解由小路在富|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kadenokōji Akitomi|qq=}}, a noble of the {{ill|Kamo clan|ja|賀茂朝臣氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo clan|qq=}} lineage residing in [[:en:Sagami Province|Sagami Province]], was summoned to Kyoto to take over the Onmyōryō's responsibilities.

== Lineage ==
=== Family===
* Father: {{ill|Tsuchimikado Ariharu|ja|土御門有春|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado Ariharu|qq=}}
* Mother: Unknown
* Wife: Seishunin
* Children:
''' {{ill|Tsuchimikado Hisanaga|ja|土御門久脩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado Hisanaga|qq=}}
''' Daughter: Married to {{ill|Kanjūji Harutoyo|ja|勧修寺晴豊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjūji Harutoyo|qq=}}

=== Descendants===
The male-line descendants of [[:en:Abe no Seimei|Abe no Seimei]] through Tsuchimikado Arinaga have largely been lost. Notably, the {{ill|Kurahashi family|ja|倉橋家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurahashi family|qq=}} (a cadet branch of the Abe clan) and the {{ill|Kanjūji family|ja|勧修寺家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjūji family|qq=}} trace their lineage through Arinaga's children and subsequent marriages. The family line continued through daughter’s descendants and their connections to prominent aristocratic families, including the [[:en:Imperial House of Japan|Imperial House of Japan]] from [[:en:Emperor Ninkō|Emperor Ninkō]] onwards.

